ields by Nomoto et al.\n(1997) and Limongi and Chieffi (2003) for massive stars and discussed the\ncorrections required in these yields in order to fit the observations. Finally,\nthe small spread in the [el/Fe] ratios in the metallicity range from\n[Fe/H]=-4.0 up to -3.0 dex (Cayrel et al. 2003) is a clear sign that the halo\nof the Milky Way was well mixed even in the earliest phases of its evolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 23 Jan 2004 14:07:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 16 Feb 2004 15:24:43 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 16 Apr 2004 10:30:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
